title: Last second field goal lifts West Johnston past East Wake
text:
Last second field goal lifts West Johnston past East Wake 
Posted 4:16 a.m. today Your friends e-mail addresses (comma separated): * Subject: * You must enter the characters with black color that stand out from the other characters More on this 61 Images 
Benson, N.C. â€” A Christian Torres field goal as time expired gave West Johnston a big 29-26 win over East Wake on Thursday night. 
The two teams entered the second quarter in a 6-6 tie, but West Johnston took its first lead of the game in the second quarter when Tony Mack broke a seven-yard run for a score. The two-point conversion attempt failed, and West Johnston led 12-6. 
East Wake tied the game on a Mikekale Engles run later in the quarter. Then Chris Ajagbawa caught a 20-yard touchdown pass from Tripp Harrington to give East Wake another lead at 18-12. 
But West Johnston didn't back down. 
The Wildcats struck first in the second half as Jake Strickland caught a pass from Andre Wilson for a touchdown. The extra-point from Torres was good this time, and West Johnston led 19-18. 
This game went back-and-forth throughout. Engles answered with a long touchdown run to give East Wake another lead, then Wilson scored again for West Johnston. The two teams were tied at 26-26 late in the fourth quarter. 
With time running out, Torres came on the field to attempt a 25-yard field goal in the final seconds. After missing an extra-point earlier in the day, the field goal was good and West Johnston left with the win. 
The win was a big win for West Johnston, which is now 3-4 overall and 2-1 in the Greater Neuse River Conference. East Wake falls to 3-3 overall and 1-1 in the league.
